
[1]remonstrate

   REMON'STRATE, v.i. [L. remonstro; re and monstro, to show. See Muster.]

   1. To exhibit or present strong reasons against an act, measure of any
   course of proceedings; to expostulate. Men remonstrate by verbal
   argument, or by a written exposition of reasons.

   2. To suggest urgent reasons in opposition to a measure. conscience
   remonstrates against a profligate life.

      REMON'STRATE, v.t. To show by a strong representation of reasons.
